WEBVTT

00:02.040 --> 00:03.920
Mellie. Answer me.

00:05.670 --> 00:06.830
What did you do?

00:06.830 --> 00:09.170
What I had to do.

00:09.170 --> 00:12.120
You had to make Jake
your Chief of Staff?

00:12.120 --> 00:13.330
Please tell me.
After everything --

00:13.330 --> 00:14.830
Please tell me
you are not this stupid.

00:14.830 --> 00:15.790
Stupid?

00:15.790 --> 00:18.000
And naive and reckless

00:18.000 --> 00:20.000
and foolish,
but most of all, stupid.

00:20.000 --> 00:21.830
You wanna know what
stupid would be, Olivia?

00:21.830 --> 00:24.920
Allowing myself to continue
believing all of your lies.

00:24.920 --> 00:26.290
Proceeding to play

00:26.290 --> 00:27.250
this great big
game of pretend

00:27.250 --> 00:29.290
that you have so
skillfully set up.

00:29.290 --> 00:30.620
I would be stupid

00:30.620 --> 00:33.120
if, for one more second,

00:33.120 --> 00:36.170
I actually trusted
that there is only us.

00:36.170 --> 00:37.920
That you and I are sisters

00:37.920 --> 00:39.670
just out there,
doin' it for themselves.

00:39.670 --> 00:41.290
Can you imagine?

00:41.290 --> 00:43.500
I assume
he showed you the kill folder.

00:43.500 --> 00:46.380
Mm.
Jake Ballard has his own
motives, Madam President,

00:46.380 --> 00:48.170
his own complexes.

00:48.170 --> 00:50.460
This isn't about some
silly little folder, Olivia.

00:50.460 --> 00:52.330
This is about
you killing Rashad.

00:52.330 --> 00:56.250
Yes.

00:56.250 --> 01:00.290
I killed Rashad,
but, Mellie, you know why.

01:00.290 --> 01:02.540
You said
you wanted that treaty.

01:02.540 --> 01:05.620
You said --
No more lies.

01:05.620 --> 01:07.960
What is it with you?
I'm not --

01:07.960 --> 01:11.000
You didn't kill Rashad
for a treaty.

01:11.000 --> 01:12.750
You didn't kill him
for peace in the Middle East.

01:12.750 --> 01:14.290
You didn't even kill him

01:14.290 --> 01:16.790
because you thought
Rashad was a bad man.

01:16.790 --> 01:22.250
You killed him because you
thought I was a bad president.

01:24.380 --> 01:25.830
You know what?

01:25.830 --> 01:27.790
We don't have to do this.

01:37.670 --> 01:40.170
[ Sighs ]

01:44.080 --> 01:45.380
Mellie.

01:45.380 --> 01:46.670
You have to go.

01:46.670 --> 01:47.710
You're angry.

01:47.710 --> 01:49.460
I get that.
I'm not angry.

01:49.460 --> 01:51.790
It would be a mistake
to allow that anger

01:51.790 --> 01:53.830
to cloud what is
really happening here.

01:53.830 --> 01:56.250
This is Jake coming between us,
getting in your head.

01:56.250 --> 01:58.250
Don't let --
I'm not angry.

01:58.250 --> 02:00.120
Or confused.

02:00.120 --> 02:02.790
Olivia, you have to go.

02:02.790 --> 02:08.790
♪♪

02:10.790 --> 02:12.040
Don't do this.

02:14.040 --> 02:15.580
Don't do this.

02:15.580 --> 02:21.580
♪♪

02:23.620 --> 02:24.920
[ Sighs ]

02:24.920 --> 02:26.790
[ Breathes deeply ]

02:26.790 --> 02:31.380
♪♪

02:31.380 --> 02:32.920
You have until the end
of the week

02:32.920 --> 02:34.500
to announce
your resignation.

02:34.500 --> 02:37.540
If for some reason
you choose not to do that,

02:37.540 --> 02:39.500
I march
into the briefing room,

02:39.500 --> 02:41.500
and I announce
your termination.

02:41.500 --> 02:45.750
♪♪

02:45.750 --> 02:47.500
You have to go.

02:47.500 --> 02:53.500
♪♪

02:57.500 --> 03:03.500
♪♪

03:03.670 --> 03:05.670
♪♪

03:16.120 --> 03:19.580
Washington is abuzz this morning
over unconfirmed reports

03:19.580 --> 03:23.170
that Olivia Pope is out
as White House Chief of Staff.

03:23.170 --> 03:24.620
There has been
no official comment

03:24.620 --> 03:26.040
from the Grant Administration,

03:26.040 --> 03:28.210
which has only solidified
the rumor

03:28.210 --> 03:32.380
among Washington insiders, many
of whom are already speculating

03:32.380 --> 03:34.620
about who Ms. Pope's
replacement might be

03:34.620 --> 03:36.420
if the reports
are, indeed, true.

03:36.420 --> 03:38.170
Chief of Staff?

03:38.170 --> 03:39.580
You should be so proud,
baby.

03:39.580 --> 03:41.790
Now, I know you've
been vetted before, Jake.

03:41.790 --> 03:43.170
But, still,
I have to ask --

03:43.170 --> 03:44.420
Is there anything we need
to know about --

03:44.420 --> 03:47.420
anything we could've missed
previously?

03:47.420 --> 03:50.420
Vanessa and I
have an open marriage.

03:50.420 --> 03:51.580
Jake.
I see.

03:51.580 --> 03:54.080
A-A-And by "open marriage,"
you mean --

03:54.080 --> 03:55.580
She's been sleeping
with someone else.

03:55.580 --> 03:58.420
Is.
Is sleeping with someone else.

03:58.420 --> 04:00.330
Wow. So we're just gonna
put it all out there.

04:00.330 --> 04:02.710
We have a deal.
It works.

04:02.710 --> 04:04.170
It shouldn't be
any concern.

04:04.170 --> 04:05.500
We're careful.
Exceedingly so.

04:05.500 --> 04:06.670
But in the interest
of transparency,

04:06.670 --> 04:07.750
I think it's something
you should know.

04:07.750 --> 04:09.170
Shouldn't be a big deal.

04:09.170 --> 04:11.500
Not like
you asked Russian hookers

04:11.500 --> 04:13.000
to pee on you or something.
[ Chuckles ]

04:13.000 --> 04:14.000
[ Breathes sharply ]

04:14.000 --> 04:15.960
[ Breathes deeply ]

04:15.960 --> 04:17.250
Chief of Staff, Nessa.

04:17.250 --> 04:19.040
We're finally getting
what we want.

04:19.040 --> 04:22.250
You should be
just as proud as me.

04:22.250 --> 04:23.830
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

04:23.830 --> 04:26.540
As long as she held all
the cards, our hands were tied.

04:26.540 --> 04:28.710
But there's a window now.
We have a chance.

04:28.710 --> 04:30.540
We can bring a case against
her. Put her away for good.

04:30.540 --> 04:32.500
Without the White House in
her corner, we have a real shot.

04:32.500 --> 04:34.120
Because she no longer
runs the Oval.
Yes.

04:34.120 --> 04:36.750
And you know that because?
What?

04:36.750 --> 04:38.580
How do you know
she no longer runs the Oval?

04:38.580 --> 04:39.920
We saw it.

04:39.920 --> 04:41.040
You were just sitting
next to me.

04:41.040 --> 04:41.790
We both saw it on the news.

04:41.790 --> 04:43.080
And who makes the news?

04:43.080 --> 04:44.920
Who bends the media
to her will?

04:44.920 --> 04:46.170
Who creates the stories
that are witnessed

04:46.170 --> 04:47.710
and reported
and fed to the public?

04:47.710 --> 04:50.210
Who decides
what reality is?

04:50.210 --> 04:51.540
"We solve problems,
manage crises,

04:51.540 --> 04:52.920
save reputations," damn it.

04:52.920 --> 04:55.460
Yeah, if the giant is down,
it's not because she's dead.

04:55.460 --> 04:57.710
The giant is licking its wounds,
but only for a moment.

04:57.710 --> 04:59.330
She will rise again.

04:59.330 --> 05:01.500
That's all the more reason
why we act now.

05:01.500 --> 05:03.170
Before she rallies
and our window closes.

05:03.170 --> 05:04.920
No.
No, I don't think so.

05:04.920 --> 05:05.920
But --
No.

05:05.920 --> 05:07.460
I just -- I --
No!

05:07.460 --> 05:09.500
[ Water running ]

05:11.710 --> 05:15.750
♪♪

05:15.750 --> 05:18.120
[ Running stops ]

05:18.120 --> 05:19.750
♪♪

05:19.750 --> 05:21.040
Abby.

05:21.040 --> 05:22.960
You heard? About Liv?
You kidding?

05:22.960 --> 05:25.750
My Olivia Pope Google Alert went
bonkers maybe two hours ago.

05:25.750 --> 05:26.920
I have a call in to David

05:26.920 --> 05:28.500
to see if there's any truth
to the rumors.

05:28.500 --> 05:29.880
-Who's the guy?
-He's from the State Department.

05:29.880 --> 05:31.960
He's a client.
Or potential.

05:31.960 --> 05:33.960
I know you're grieving.
We all are.

05:33.960 --> 05:35.330
But the firm is strapped.

05:35.330 --> 05:36.960
So we either need
to take on new clients

05:36.960 --> 05:38.460
or start talking
about closing up shop.

05:38.460 --> 05:40.620
Which, with Quinn's death --
No, no. No, no.

05:40.620 --> 05:42.540
I-I think Quinn would want us
to do whatever it takes

05:42.540 --> 05:43.920
to stay in business.

05:43.920 --> 05:46.750
But maybe we want to swing for
someone with deeper pockets.

05:46.750 --> 05:48.540
Government employees?

05:48.540 --> 05:50.330
Not exactly rolling in dough.

05:50.330 --> 05:53.620
-Funny you should say that.
-It's insane.

05:53.620 --> 05:56.420
I-I wouldn't have even known
anything was wrong

05:56.420 --> 05:58.500
except I-I wanted to get
a hot dog, you know,

05:58.500 --> 06:00.290
from the guy with the cart
outside my office,

06:00.290 --> 06:02.960
and I didn't have any cash,
so I hit ATM on Mass. Ave.

06:02.960 --> 06:05.380
And when I looked at
the balance on my statement,

06:05.380 --> 06:07.120
I just about crapped myself.

06:07.120 --> 06:08.960
I would've, too.
$12 million?

06:08.960 --> 06:10.210
$12 million.

06:10.210 --> 06:11.380
I told the bank about it.

06:11.380 --> 06:12.750
They said
it wasn't a mistake.

06:12.750 --> 06:14.290
The transaction was legit.

06:14.290 --> 06:16.580
Which made absolutely no sense
to me whatsoever

06:16.580 --> 06:19.460
until I checked my e-mail.

06:19.460 --> 06:21.540
This is in Russian.

06:21.540 --> 06:24.380
♪♪

06:24.380 --> 06:26.170
"Mr. Bacall, you are
now in our service.

06:26.170 --> 06:27.830
Please enjoy
your signing bonus.

06:27.830 --> 06:30.040
We'll be in contact
with further instructions."

06:30.040 --> 06:32.790
I just can't figure out
why they would want me.

06:32.790 --> 06:34.670
You do work
in the State Department.

06:34.670 --> 06:36.460
Yeah, mid-level.

06:36.460 --> 06:38.710
I haven't had a promotion
in six years.

06:38.710 --> 06:41.250
I'm -- I'm nobody.

06:41.250 --> 06:43.210
This makes me out to be
some kind of super-spy.

06:43.210 --> 06:44.830
I can't figure it out.

06:44.830 --> 06:46.670
I should have plenty of time
while I'm spending the rest

06:46.670 --> 06:48.330
of my life behind bars
for treason.

06:48.330 --> 06:51.710
Look.
I like my life the way it is.

06:51.710 --> 06:55.210
It's small, but it's mine.

06:55.210 --> 06:58.460
Please. I just want
all of this to go away.

06:58.460 --> 06:59.540
Can you do that?

06:59.540 --> 07:01.880
♪♪

07:01.880 --> 07:04.540
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

07:04.540 --> 07:07.120
[ Door opens ]

07:08.290 --> 07:11.000
Madam President.
Thank you for coming.

07:11.000 --> 07:13.290
I know our working relationship
is evolving, Jake,

07:13.290 --> 07:16.330
but to be clear, I am
not someone you can summon.

07:16.330 --> 07:18.460
Oh, apologies.
No, that wasn't the idea.

07:18.460 --> 07:20.080
What?

07:20.080 --> 07:22.170
Our relationship
is evolving.

07:22.170 --> 07:24.330
If I'm gonna be
your Chief of Staff in command,

07:24.330 --> 07:26.210
I want to start from a place
of trust. Full transparency.

07:26.210 --> 07:28.960
This isn't
Olivia's B613 anymore.

07:28.960 --> 07:32.040
My intel is your intel.
My tools are your tools.

07:32.040 --> 07:33.250
[ Static crackles ]

07:33.250 --> 07:35.620
[ Breathes deeply ]

07:35.620 --> 07:38.540
Maybe we better get you
some better tools.

07:38.540 --> 07:41.000
[ Static crackles, beeping ]

07:41.000 --> 07:47.000
♪♪

07:47.330 --> 07:49.120
[ Cellphone chimes ]

07:49.120 --> 07:53.790
♪♪

07:53.790 --> 07:56.580
[ Chiming continues ]

07:56.580 --> 08:00.040
♪♪

08:00.040 --> 08:02.120
This is Olivia.

08:02.120 --> 08:03.080
You really don't want
to do this.

08:03.080 --> 08:06.330
[ Chuckles ]
I really, really do.

08:06.330 --> 08:08.290
This only ends one way,
and you know it:

08:08.290 --> 08:09.330
You lose.

08:09.330 --> 08:10.750
You took Chief of Staff.

08:10.750 --> 08:12.460
It was a good move.
Well-played.

08:12.460 --> 08:14.080
But you forgot one thing.

08:14.080 --> 08:14.960
Oh, yeah?
What's that?

08:14.960 --> 08:17.210
You can't take Command.

08:17.210 --> 08:18.670
[ Sighs ]

08:18.670 --> 08:19.920
♪♪

08:25.290 --> 08:27.000
Can't you just reboot the entire
system to flush out the virus?

08:27.000 --> 08:28.290
I could if it were a virus.
But this?

08:28.290 --> 08:30.580
This looks
more like phreaking.

08:30.580 --> 08:31.580
"Freaking"?

08:31.580 --> 08:33.380
"Phreaking."
With a P-H.

08:33.380 --> 08:35.330
Back in the '80s,
hackers used a whistle

08:35.330 --> 08:37.880
that came in a box of
Cap'n Crunch to break into AT&T

08:37.880 --> 08:38.960
and get
free long distance.

08:38.960 --> 08:41.170
It's very old school.

08:41.170 --> 08:43.580
You're tell me the most
sophisticated computers

08:43.580 --> 08:45.620
in the world were brought down
with a toy whistle?

08:45.620 --> 08:48.670
I'm saying whoever did this
wasn't born yesterday.

08:48.670 --> 08:51.080
[ Sighs ]

08:51.080 --> 08:52.620
♪♪

08:52.620 --> 08:54.500
[ Sighs ]

08:54.500 --> 08:56.250
Olivia: Hector.

08:56.250 --> 09:00.330
Shouldn't you have a team of
armed guards with you, lady?

09:00.330 --> 09:02.250
We turned
those fools' lights off.

09:02.250 --> 09:04.120
No way
they're not coming after you.

09:04.120 --> 09:05.670
It's just Jake and
a skeleton crew back there.

09:05.670 --> 09:07.420
The real guns and money
are still with me.

09:07.420 --> 09:09.210
How long can we keep 'em
off the network?

09:09.210 --> 09:10.670
How long do you need?

09:10.670 --> 09:13.000
As long as it takes for him
to come to his senses.

09:13.000 --> 09:14.710
Well, that's asking
a whole lot.

09:14.710 --> 09:16.120
My father said
you can do anything.

09:19.000 --> 09:21.120
Have you talked to him
lately?

09:21.120 --> 09:23.290
He and I
didn't end so good.

09:23.290 --> 09:26.170
He and I
didn't end so good, either.

09:26.170 --> 09:27.710
Let me see what I can do.

09:27.710 --> 09:29.170
Good. "Phase 2"?

09:29.170 --> 09:30.500
Just waiting
for your green light.

09:32.500 --> 09:33.670
She's having a tantrum.

09:33.670 --> 09:35.120
Once the system
is back up and running,

09:35.120 --> 09:36.330
I'll put some surveillance
on her.

09:36.330 --> 09:37.710
Make sure she doesn't do
anything to embarrass us.

09:37.710 --> 09:39.420
That is not a tantrum.

09:39.420 --> 09:40.880
That is a hungry lion
loose in a preschool.
[ Door opens ]

09:40.880 --> 09:43.500
Vice President Beene is asking
to have a minute of your time.

09:43.500 --> 09:45.540
Send him in.

09:45.540 --> 09:47.210
Shut it down.

09:48.790 --> 09:50.170
Mr. Vice President.

09:50.170 --> 09:51.000
Admiral.

09:56.460 --> 09:59.330
Stopped by to tighten
the screws, did he?

09:59.330 --> 10:01.420
-What are you talking about?
-Ballard.

10:04.540 --> 10:06.790
What's he got on you?

10:06.790 --> 10:08.580
Is it K-Karen?

10:08.580 --> 10:10.120
Did she get
in trouble again?

10:10.120 --> 10:12.080
Is he using your family
against you?

10:12.080 --> 10:14.170
Tell me what it is.
I can help you.

10:14.170 --> 10:16.210
Incredible.

10:16.210 --> 10:17.960
Why does everyone assume
that I'm the victim?

10:17.960 --> 10:19.380
[ Scoffs ]

10:19.380 --> 10:21.750
Jake is still here
because I want him here.

10:21.750 --> 10:23.880
Not because he has
something over me.

10:23.880 --> 10:27.080
This is the man
who killed Rashad.

10:27.080 --> 10:30.620
At Olivia's request.

10:30.620 --> 10:32.710
At Olivia...

10:32.710 --> 10:34.580
Request?

10:34.580 --> 10:36.920
[ Sighs ]

10:36.920 --> 10:40.670
We should be giving that man
a potassium-chloride injection.

10:40.670 --> 10:43.120
Not a promotion!

10:43.120 --> 10:46.250
What the hell
is wrong with you?!

10:46.250 --> 10:47.960
Liv is out, and Jake is in.

10:47.960 --> 10:49.580
That is
all you need to know.

10:49.580 --> 10:52.250
So either get on board
and be my vice president

10:52.250 --> 10:54.380
or be someone
that I have to deal with.

10:54.380 --> 10:57.710
But I promise you.

10:57.710 --> 11:00.120
You do not want to be someone
that I have to deal with.

11:00.120 --> 11:01.580
Not today.

11:01.580 --> 11:07.580
♪♪

11:10.120 --> 11:12.460
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

11:12.460 --> 11:15.500
Rowan: You have
a very large head, little one.

11:15.500 --> 11:17.540
Which is very, very good.

11:17.540 --> 11:20.920
Because it means
you have a very big brain.

11:20.920 --> 11:22.540
[ Chuckles ] Yes.

11:22.540 --> 11:24.080
Yeah.

11:26.500 --> 11:28.830
Yep. Oh, yeah.

11:28.830 --> 11:31.250
[ Chuckles ]

11:31.250 --> 11:33.710
My daughter
had a very large head

11:33.710 --> 11:35.710
and a very large brain,
so...

11:35.710 --> 11:37.460
[ Laughs ]
Mm-hmm.

11:37.460 --> 11:38.920
So you're in good company.

11:38.920 --> 11:41.000
-[ Coos ]
-Mm-hmm.

11:41.000 --> 11:43.250
I'm not sure who's enjoying
that more. You or her.

11:43.250 --> 11:45.960
To be honest, me either.

11:45.960 --> 11:47.170
[ Sighs ]

11:47.170 --> 11:48.580
I've gotta ask --
Is this why?

11:48.580 --> 11:50.330
Is what why?

11:50.330 --> 11:52.120
Is this
why you're in denial?

11:52.120 --> 11:54.540
You know
this is our moment.

11:54.540 --> 11:56.880
That we have a real shot
at taking Olivia down.

11:56.880 --> 11:59.710
But you also know that if we do
that, Robin and I will leave,

11:59.710 --> 12:01.330
and your house
will be empty again.

12:01.330 --> 12:02.960
You don't know
what you're talking about.

12:02.960 --> 12:05.250
You like having us here.

12:05.250 --> 12:06.710
You like having
a baby in your house.

12:06.710 --> 12:08.920
You're happy.

12:08.920 --> 12:10.380
And it's making you soft.

12:10.380 --> 12:13.210
Soft?

12:13.210 --> 12:16.460
You're losing sight
of the goal.

12:16.460 --> 12:19.380
I'm sorry. I know you don't
want to hear it, but...

12:19.380 --> 12:22.290
we are not your family.

12:22.290 --> 12:24.170
We are not here
to play house.

12:24.170 --> 12:26.120
We are here
because Olivia is --

12:26.120 --> 12:28.790
I said, "That's enough."

12:28.790 --> 12:31.830
You don't want to play tough
with me, girl.

12:31.830 --> 12:34.000
Don't push me.

12:34.000 --> 12:38.080
Not while I have your child
in my hands.

12:38.080 --> 12:39.920
[ Robin coos ]
Mm.

12:39.920 --> 12:44.330
If there's anyone here
who's misreading the situation,

12:44.330 --> 12:46.250
it's you.

12:46.250 --> 12:47.670
[ Coos ]

12:47.670 --> 12:50.460
You say I've gone "soft"?

12:50.460 --> 12:53.290
Hardly.

12:53.290 --> 12:56.460
This child...

12:56.460 --> 12:59.500
This child is soft.

12:59.500 --> 13:01.040
[ Chuckles ]

13:01.040 --> 13:05.380
And her neck is very soft.

13:05.380 --> 13:11.380
Imagine if I took my hand --
this hand --

13:11.420 --> 13:14.670
and began to apply pressure
right here.

13:14.670 --> 13:15.750
How would you feel
about that?

13:15.750 --> 13:16.830
Don't!

13:16.830 --> 13:18.210
I haven't done a thing.

13:18.210 --> 13:20.670
And, still, you feel it,
don't you?

13:20.670 --> 13:24.120
That nausea rising up,
deep in the pit of your stomach,

13:24.120 --> 13:25.500
right up to the back
of your throat

13:25.500 --> 13:29.670
just at the idea someone
might hurt your child.

13:29.670 --> 13:31.000
That's biology.

13:31.000 --> 13:35.290
That's Mother Nature's
special little trick.

13:35.290 --> 13:38.790
I know
you want to take Olivia down.

13:38.790 --> 13:41.500
I won't allow it.

13:41.500 --> 13:43.290
I can't.

13:43.290 --> 13:45.750
Because of my biology,

13:45.750 --> 13:47.790
because of my nature,

13:47.790 --> 13:50.170
I can't let
anyone hurt my child

13:50.170 --> 13:52.920
any more than you would abide
someone hurting yours.

13:52.920 --> 13:54.330
[ Crying ]

13:54.330 --> 13:55.500
You give her to me!

13:55.500 --> 14:01.500
♪♪

14:02.670 --> 14:08.670
♪♪

14:09.710 --> 14:15.750
♪♪

14:17.040 --> 14:19.460
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

14:19.460 --> 14:21.540
Huck, you've been tracing that
Russian e-mail for an hour.

14:21.540 --> 14:22.790
You have to have found
something.

14:22.790 --> 14:24.380
I'm finding plenty.

14:24.380 --> 14:26.210
This thing's got a trail,

14:26.210 --> 14:28.620
but it's a trail that keeps
leading in circles.

14:28.620 --> 14:29.920
And every time
I think I'm about

14:29.920 --> 14:31.210
to figure out
exactly who sent it,

14:31.210 --> 14:32.960
I end up
right back where I started.

14:32.960 --> 14:35.040
It's really impressive.

14:35.040 --> 14:36.920
Okay. Robert, buddy,
you got to give us more info.

14:36.920 --> 14:38.790
I have told you everything.

14:38.790 --> 14:40.000
There's gotta be something
you're leaving out.

14:40.000 --> 14:41.580
Abby:
Boy, I'll say there is.

14:41.580 --> 14:43.120
Hotel receipts.

14:43.120 --> 14:44.960
Dozens and dozens
of midday meetings

14:44.960 --> 14:46.580
that seem to have
slipped your mind.

14:46.580 --> 14:48.120
A-All right. That's --
That's -- That's nothing.

14:48.120 --> 14:49.380
That doesn't seem
like nothing.

14:49.380 --> 14:50.460
Seems like
you've been having meetings

14:50.460 --> 14:51.460
that you don't
want us to know about.

14:51.460 --> 14:53.000
Seems like
you've walked in here

14:53.000 --> 14:54.620
acting like
a little lost innocent

14:54.620 --> 14:55.920
when, actually,
you've been getting up

14:55.920 --> 14:57.000
to something you shouldn't.

14:57.000 --> 14:58.540
No, no.
You've got it wrong.

14:58.540 --> 14:59.670
Is she wrong, though?

14:59.670 --> 15:01.290
Because if she isn't,
you should tell us.

15:01.290 --> 15:03.540
It's not a deal breaker.
Charlie, it's treason.

15:03.540 --> 15:05.170
Like you've never committed
a little treason.

15:05.170 --> 15:06.420
It isn't treason!

15:08.080 --> 15:10.120
I'm having an affair,
okay?

15:10.120 --> 15:12.330
I'm sleeping
with a married woman.

15:12.330 --> 15:14.330
Um, guys.
So why didn't
you just say that?

15:14.330 --> 15:15.960
Because it isn't
any of your business.

15:15.960 --> 15:17.460
It isn't pertinent.
She's not even Russian!

15:17.460 --> 15:19.120
-Guys. Guys!
-Who is she?

15:19.120 --> 15:20.880
Woman: ...Robert Bacall is being
identified as the source...

15:20.880 --> 15:22.620
He's sleeping
with Vanessa Ballard.

15:22.620 --> 15:25.330
We're hearing from our sources
that Mr. Bacall

15:25.330 --> 15:28.670
has been feeding intelligence
to Russian agents,

15:28.670 --> 15:30.830
using his position
at the State Department

15:30.830 --> 15:34.000
and his secret relationship
with Vanessa Ballard --

15:34.000 --> 15:36.670
wife of NSA Director
Jake Ballard --

15:36.670 --> 15:39.000
to access state secrets.

15:39.000 --> 15:41.670
Now, the scope and seriousness
of these breaches...

15:41.670 --> 15:43.040
You've been sleeping
with a woman

15:43.040 --> 15:45.330
who's married to the head
of the National Security Agency,

15:45.330 --> 15:47.330
and somehow you didn't think
that was pertinent?

15:47.330 --> 15:50.710
...$12 billion being paid
to him directly.

15:50.710 --> 15:53.420
Through her husband's
employment at the NSA,

15:53.420 --> 15:55.420
Vanessa Ballard
could have had access

15:55.420 --> 15:57.710
to a panoply of state secrets.

15:57.710 --> 16:00.500
[ Cellphone chiming ]
In his capacity as NSA Chief,

16:00.500 --> 16:03.460
Admiral Ballard oversees
the gathering and analysis

16:03.460 --> 16:05.420
of foreign intelligence
as part of his...

16:05.420 --> 16:06.830
I wrote a draft
of your resignation letter.

16:06.830 --> 16:07.920
Tell me what you think.

16:07.920 --> 16:10.170
You're attacking my wife now?

16:10.170 --> 16:11.750
"In light
of the ongoing investigation

16:11.750 --> 16:13.960
into my wife, Vanessa..."
Command has dignity.

16:13.960 --> 16:15.670
"...I've decided
to withdraw my name

16:15.670 --> 16:17.920
from consideration
for the job of Chief of Staff."

16:17.920 --> 16:19.710
Command has pride.

16:19.710 --> 16:22.250
"I also resign as Director of
the National Security Agency..."

16:22.250 --> 16:23.790
This needs to end!
Do you hear me?

16:23.790 --> 16:26.500
"...and will surrender
my security clearance unt--"

16:26.500 --> 16:32.080
♪♪

16:37.380 --> 16:39.170
I was promised
a smooth transition.

16:39.170 --> 16:40.790
And now it would seem
that the wife

16:40.790 --> 16:43.330
of my pick for Chief of Staff
is not just having an affair --

16:43.330 --> 16:45.670
[Laughing] She's allegedly
selling state secrets

16:45.670 --> 16:47.830
to the highest bidder!
S-She's not selling
state secrets.

16:47.830 --> 16:49.920
She's just having
an affair.
I don't believe it.

16:49.920 --> 16:51.210
We're launching
a full-scale investigation

16:51.210 --> 16:53.330
into the matter,
Madam President.

16:53.330 --> 16:54.880
If there's any
evidence of a breach in
our national security --

16:54.880 --> 16:58.080
Our national security is intact,
Madam President, I assure you.

16:58.080 --> 16:59.670
I can also assure you
my wife is not spy

16:59.670 --> 17:01.620
and Bob Bacall has never
freelanced for the Russians.

17:01.620 --> 17:03.750
Then how did that money
get in his account?

17:03.750 --> 17:05.120
Olivia Pope, Rosen.

17:05.120 --> 17:06.210
She's framing him
for espionage.

17:06.210 --> 17:07.750
Olivia Pope.
Madam President --

17:07.750 --> 17:09.170
Enough!

17:14.170 --> 17:16.750
Today was supposed to be
a good day.

17:16.750 --> 17:18.380
I was looking forward
to today.

17:18.380 --> 17:21.580
Today was the day I was supposed
to get my yearly mammogram.

17:21.580 --> 17:22.920
Do you know how long
I've been waiting

17:22.920 --> 17:24.580
to get my yearly mammogram?

17:26.380 --> 17:28.670
Since I moved into the place.

17:28.670 --> 17:31.670
Because apparently
no one's ever had to schedule

17:31.670 --> 17:33.920
one of those things
for any other sitting president.

17:33.920 --> 17:36.670
Go figure. And it's not like
there's a mammography machine

17:36.670 --> 17:38.040
in the White House Medical Unit.

17:38.040 --> 17:39.920
Damn thing would just be
sitting there, collecting dust!

17:39.920 --> 17:44.830
[ Sighs ]

17:44.830 --> 17:46.250
Ballard is right, Rosen.

17:46.250 --> 17:47.790
This was Olivia Pope.

17:47.790 --> 17:50.750
So launch your investigation
and prove it.

17:50.750 --> 17:53.460
Then make it go away.

17:53.460 --> 17:55.670
Don't ruin this day for me,
gentlemen.

17:58.540 --> 17:59.620
You can go.

17:59.620 --> 18:02.670
Yes, ma'am.
Madam President.

18:02.670 --> 18:04.920
[ Door opens ]
[ Sighs ]

18:04.920 --> 18:06.880
[ Door closes ]

18:06.880 --> 18:10.000
♪♪

18:14.830 --> 18:17.960
Drinking alone?

18:17.960 --> 18:20.790
Celebrating, actually.

18:20.790 --> 18:22.750
Don't know if you heard,

18:22.750 --> 18:25.040
but Mellie's let
her Chief of Staff go.

18:25.040 --> 18:26.620
Has she?

18:30.120 --> 18:32.000
You gonna offer me
one of those?

18:32.000 --> 18:33.500
Wish I could.

18:33.500 --> 18:36.330
Unfortunately,
I don't drink with my enemies.

18:40.170 --> 18:42.290
I'm sorry about
what happened with Fenton.

18:42.290 --> 18:44.880
If I had had other options,
I'd have taken them.

18:44.880 --> 18:46.880
Ah!

18:46.880 --> 18:48.170
At least it worked.

18:48.170 --> 18:51.830
Killing Rashad came
with a peace treaty attached.

18:51.830 --> 18:54.210
I did everything I had to do
to protect that.

18:54.210 --> 18:56.210
You've done far worse
for much less.

19:02.790 --> 19:04.960
This story about Vanessa.

19:04.960 --> 19:06.460
I take it that's you?

19:06.460 --> 19:07.790
There's a coup
in the White House.

19:07.790 --> 19:09.830
Jake made his move.
Now I've made mine.

19:09.830 --> 19:12.420
Well,
I admire your confidence.

19:12.420 --> 19:14.120
Most people
who take on the U.S. government

19:14.120 --> 19:16.170
show a little more humility.

19:16.170 --> 19:18.080
You have some secret weapon
nobody knows about?

19:18.080 --> 19:19.080
You.

19:19.080 --> 19:21.710
[ Scoffs ] Me?

19:21.710 --> 19:23.540
[ Breathes deeply ]

19:23.540 --> 19:25.170
Why would I ever help you?

19:25.170 --> 19:27.210
Because you're an adult.

19:27.210 --> 19:30.000
You know
how the world works.

19:30.000 --> 19:32.500
And deep down, you know
what I did was right,

19:32.500 --> 19:34.960
because it's exactly
what you would have done.

19:34.960 --> 19:38.210
Mellie's lost, Cyrus.

19:38.210 --> 19:41.170
She's listening
to Jake Ballard, of all people.

19:41.170 --> 19:42.290
Jake Ballard.

19:42.290 --> 19:44.250
And if he managed
to push me out,

19:44.250 --> 19:46.420
don't think
he won't do the same to you.

19:46.420 --> 19:48.080
♪♪

19:48.080 --> 19:50.460
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

19:50.460 --> 19:52.000
[ Keyboard clacking ]

20:01.420 --> 20:03.710
I'm very sorry.

20:03.710 --> 20:06.040
Really. A-A-About all of --
Robert. No.

20:12.000 --> 20:14.500
Vanessa said
you wouldn't mind.

20:14.500 --> 20:18.290
Otherwise, I-I-I wouldn't --
I never would ha--

20:23.000 --> 20:25.750
How hard is it to prove the
money in Robert's bank account

20:25.750 --> 20:27.540
is from Olivia
and not the Russians?

20:27.540 --> 20:28.830
Very.

20:28.830 --> 20:30.670
Oh, was that
a rhetorical question?

20:30.670 --> 20:32.710
We've tried tracing the money
a bunch of different ways,

20:32.710 --> 20:33.790
and even the reverse

20:33.790 --> 20:35.580
promontory point
leads directly

20:35.580 --> 20:37.330
to the Russian Foreign
Intelligence Service.

20:37.330 --> 20:38.710
Olivia's good
at covering her tracks.

20:38.710 --> 20:40.000
[ Sighs ]

20:40.000 --> 20:42.000
If we know
that this is Olivia,

20:42.000 --> 20:43.580
why can't we just leak it
to the press?

20:43.580 --> 20:45.000
Because we'd be playing
right into her hands.

20:45.000 --> 20:47.460
Going to war with Liv
in the media --

20:47.460 --> 20:48.830
her home turf --
without a single shred

20:48.830 --> 20:49.880
of evidence is pointless.

20:49.880 --> 20:52.380
She'll spin it.

20:52.380 --> 20:54.750
I lose my job.
Robert here gets the chair.

20:54.750 --> 20:55.920
We're not there yet.

20:55.920 --> 20:58.040
We'll figure something out.
Don't worry.

21:11.000 --> 21:12.500
[ Sighs ]

21:12.500 --> 21:13.620
Thank you.

21:13.620 --> 21:16.880
For including me
in your concerns.

21:16.880 --> 21:19.960
Shut up, Robert.

21:19.960 --> 21:21.120
Eat your melon.

21:25.790 --> 21:27.250
Mellie: So, it's over?

21:27.250 --> 21:28.460
This doesn't have
to end here.

21:28.460 --> 21:30.380
We can still make a case
to the American people

21:30.380 --> 21:32.380
this was a setup.
So you'd like me to out

21:32.380 --> 21:34.620
my former Chief of Staff
for framing the lover

21:34.620 --> 21:36.670
of my about-to-be
Chief of Staff's wife?

21:36.670 --> 21:38.170
Can you imagine
the blowback?!

21:38.170 --> 21:39.380
There are other options.

21:39.380 --> 21:40.670
I just need
a little more time.

21:40.670 --> 21:44.170
-I don't have any more time!
-Madam President.

21:44.170 --> 21:45.460
Jake:
Little busy right now, Cyrus.

21:45.460 --> 21:47.080
This will only take
a minute, Admiral.

21:47.080 --> 21:48.170
We are in the middle

21:48.170 --> 21:49.170
of something.

21:49.170 --> 21:51.460
And how's that something
working out?

21:51.460 --> 21:54.380
Not very well,
from the look on your faces.

21:54.380 --> 21:56.040
Cyrus.

21:56.040 --> 22:01.420
I have a way out
of this little Vanessa sitch.

22:01.420 --> 22:05.000
A way that will give Jake
his credibility back

22:05.000 --> 22:06.790
so you can appoint him
Chief of Staff

22:06.790 --> 22:08.670
with political impunity.

22:08.670 --> 22:12.330
A way that'll even make
Vanessa's affair look benign --

22:12.330 --> 22:15.540
two birds with one stone,
if you will.

22:15.540 --> 22:16.670
Would you like to hear it?

22:16.670 --> 22:17.960
Or should I come back
some other time

22:17.960 --> 22:19.120
when you're both less busy?

22:19.120 --> 22:22.250
Mm.

22:22.250 --> 22:23.500
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

22:23.500 --> 22:25.880
So, to be clear,
you are categorically denying

22:25.880 --> 22:26.880
any romantic entanglement

22:26.880 --> 22:28.920
whatsoever
with Robert Bacall,

22:28.920 --> 22:30.420
this apparent double agent?

22:30.420 --> 22:31.620
[ Chuckles ]
Goodness, yes.

22:31.620 --> 22:33.460
No, my husband is one

22:33.460 --> 22:34.880
of the highest-ranked
intelligence operatives

22:34.880 --> 22:36.580
in this country.

22:36.580 --> 22:38.120
Even if I wanted to,
do you really think

22:38.120 --> 22:39.460
that I could get away
with cheating on him?

22:39.460 --> 22:42.880
But the photos of you
entering his hotel room...

22:42.880 --> 22:45.710
Did I meet Robert Bacall
at his hotel that night? Yes.

22:45.710 --> 22:47.330
Did I accompany him
to his room? Yes.

22:47.330 --> 22:49.500
But for a tryst?

22:49.500 --> 22:50.710
No.

22:50.710 --> 22:53.210
For a sting.

22:53.210 --> 22:55.170
The NSA had suspected Robert
for months,

22:55.170 --> 22:56.790
but they needed
final proof.

22:56.790 --> 22:59.040
As it happened, he and I
knew each other socially

22:59.040 --> 23:00.710
from the campaign last year,

23:00.710 --> 23:03.750
so Jake thought that I was
the perfect woman for the job.

23:03.750 --> 23:05.620
I got to play spy.

23:05.620 --> 23:07.880
Which, let me tell you, is
not half as fun as it sounds.

23:07.880 --> 23:09.620
That wire they make you wear?
So uncomfortable.

23:09.620 --> 23:11.120
And those long,
boring conversations

23:11.120 --> 23:12.830
to gain Robert's trust?

23:12.830 --> 23:14.710
I mean, I never thought
I'd have to work so hard

23:14.710 --> 23:16.790
to seduce a man.

23:16.790 --> 23:20.040
But eventually,
that night in the hotel room,

23:20.040 --> 23:21.420
Robert did open up to me.

23:21.420 --> 23:23.380
A full confession.

23:23.380 --> 23:25.580
I think he was just
[Breathes deeply]

23:25.580 --> 23:28.920
Well, he was relieved
to have someone to confide in.

23:28.920 --> 23:30.960
And then I just told him
that I had a headache,

23:30.960 --> 23:32.580
and I got out of there.

23:32.580 --> 23:34.040
I left the rest
to the professionals.

23:34.040 --> 23:40.040
♪♪

23:41.710 --> 23:42.500
[ Clatter ]

23:49.120 --> 23:50.460
Last night, Vanessa Ballard

23:50.460 --> 23:52.330
addressed her relationship
with Robert Bacall,

23:52.330 --> 23:53.920
the State Department diplomat

23:53.920 --> 23:55.580
accused of being
a Russian operative.

23:55.580 --> 23:58.210
Speaking to Noah Baker,
Ballard revealed she was part

23:58.210 --> 24:01.250
of an intelligence sting
to expose the suspected spy.

24:01.250 --> 24:03.540
The revelation has relieved
the mounting pressure

24:03.540 --> 24:05.880
demanding the resignation
of her husband,

24:05.880 --> 24:07.960
NSA Director Jake Ballard.

24:07.960 --> 24:09.920
She just went on national TV

24:09.920 --> 24:12.830
and confirmed to the world
that I am a Russian spy.

24:12.830 --> 24:14.540
What -- What the hell
am I supposed to do now?

24:14.540 --> 24:16.000
This is a list
of defense attorneys

24:16.000 --> 24:17.620
we've used in the past.

24:17.620 --> 24:20.380
You can't go wrong
with any of them, really.

24:20.380 --> 24:22.080
Wha-- Wa--
Do -- Do you really think

24:22.080 --> 24:25.000
that the lawyers on this list
will be able to get me off?

24:26.620 --> 24:27.830
They will be able
to provide you

24:27.830 --> 24:29.750
with
the best possible defense.

24:29.750 --> 24:34.210
Or...there's a flight to
Budapest leaves in five hours.

24:34.210 --> 24:36.210
Your choice, Bob.

24:36.210 --> 24:38.080
[ Keyboard clacking ]

24:38.080 --> 24:39.420
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

24:39.420 --> 24:40.620
[ Knocking ]

24:42.460 --> 24:43.750
Bad time?

24:47.420 --> 24:49.120
[ Door closes ]

24:49.120 --> 24:50.670
Let me guess.

24:50.670 --> 24:53.500
You watched Vanessa's
interview on TV last night.

24:53.500 --> 24:55.580
Came here to dance
on my grave.

24:55.580 --> 24:58.210
Yes, I watched the interview,
but no.

24:58.210 --> 25:01.000
Dancing's
not one of my skills.

25:01.000 --> 25:05.880
A private memo written
by Mellie to the CIA Director.

25:05.880 --> 25:08.830
Asking her to corroborate
the story Vanessa Ballard

25:08.830 --> 25:11.620
told Noah Baker
last night.

25:11.620 --> 25:16.460
It's what the law calls
"obstruction of justice,"

25:16.460 --> 25:18.750
and what we fans
of werewolf literature

25:18.750 --> 25:19.830
call a "silver bullet."

25:23.710 --> 25:25.250
I can't use this.
Why?

25:25.250 --> 25:28.620
Cyrus, I asked for help
getting rid of Jake.

25:28.620 --> 25:31.170
This takes down Mellie.

25:31.170 --> 25:32.330
She'll be impeached.

25:32.330 --> 25:34.120
Yes.

25:34.120 --> 25:37.080
And guess who will be
president if that happens.

25:39.250 --> 25:41.500
You'd really do that
to her?

25:41.500 --> 25:45.540
If there's gonna be
a snake in the Oval,

25:45.540 --> 25:47.080
it might as well be me.

25:47.080 --> 25:48.290
Don't you think?

25:48.290 --> 25:49.670
Mellie is your friend.

25:49.670 --> 25:53.120
Mellie's an amateur.

25:53.120 --> 25:54.500
The poor woman.

25:54.500 --> 25:57.500
She didn't even know
I was setting her up

25:57.500 --> 26:00.080
when I suggested
the fake CIA sting

26:00.080 --> 26:02.420
as a way out of the mess
they were in.

26:02.420 --> 26:04.960
♪♪

26:04.960 --> 26:06.880
You don't need me for this.

26:06.880 --> 26:08.040
You're a big boy.

26:08.040 --> 26:09.670
You can ride this
all by yourself.

26:09.670 --> 26:10.790
It's an easy leak
to the press.

26:10.790 --> 26:11.960
Why are you here?

26:11.960 --> 26:13.460
Because you're Olivia Pope

26:13.460 --> 26:15.960
and you're better at this
than anyone else.

26:15.960 --> 26:18.170
You have the credibility.

26:18.170 --> 26:20.880
And you're the better story.

26:20.880 --> 26:24.540
Recently deposed Chief of Staff
calls a press conference.

26:24.540 --> 26:27.540
Instead of resigning,
she says she's being forced

26:27.540 --> 26:32.250
to step down as punishment
for uncovering a conspiracy.

26:32.250 --> 26:34.540
You hold up this memo,
wave it in front of the cameras.

26:34.540 --> 26:37.290
Committees are formed,
charges are filed.

26:37.290 --> 26:40.250
Next thing you know, I'm
being sworn in as president.

26:40.250 --> 26:42.500
♪♪

26:42.500 --> 26:44.670
I need you, Olivia.

26:44.670 --> 26:45.920
Just like you need me.

26:45.920 --> 26:47.710
We're parasites.

26:47.710 --> 26:51.920
Sucking each other's blood
to stay alive.

26:51.920 --> 26:57.250
♪♪

26:57.250 --> 26:59.830
This is the answer, Olivia.

27:02.250 --> 27:05.830
It's the difference
between having all the power

27:05.830 --> 27:08.960
and no power at all.

27:08.960 --> 27:10.710
Which would you prefer?

27:10.710 --> 27:16.710
♪♪

27:19.920 --> 27:22.880
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

27:26.790 --> 27:30.830
I, um...don't particularly
feel like cooking tonight.

27:30.830 --> 27:32.080
Let's order in.

27:37.620 --> 27:40.120
I am sorry, you know.

27:40.120 --> 27:42.210
I know how frustrated
you must be.

27:46.710 --> 27:49.710
Jake Ballard's wife
was on TV giving an interview.

27:49.710 --> 27:51.790
She's telling the world
she was a secret CIA operative,

27:51.790 --> 27:54.210
gathering intel.

27:54.210 --> 27:56.210
Does that mean something
to you?

27:57.880 --> 28:00.500
I think it means
Liv's still fighting.

28:00.500 --> 28:03.210
I think this was a setback,
but it's only a matter of time

28:03.210 --> 28:04.250
before she tries
something else.

28:04.250 --> 28:06.170
I also think
it's only a matter of time

28:06.170 --> 28:08.250
until she reaches out to you
for help.

28:08.250 --> 28:09.880
Which means, sooner or later,
you're going to have

28:09.880 --> 28:12.170
to choose
between Liv and us.

28:12.170 --> 28:14.170
And there is no world
where you side with us.

28:14.170 --> 28:16.750
So.
I'm making you a deal.

28:16.750 --> 28:17.920
I will call Charlie.

28:17.920 --> 28:19.460
The three of us will leave,

28:19.460 --> 28:22.080
run off to a cabin
in Pennsylvania or somewhere,

28:22.080 --> 28:24.290
and no one
will ever see us again.

28:24.290 --> 28:25.830
If you promise
to let us leave,

28:25.830 --> 28:27.420
let us live our lives,

28:27.420 --> 28:31.250
I promise
I won't go after Olivia.

28:31.250 --> 28:35.540
I will give up
the justice I deserve.

28:35.540 --> 28:37.830
If you spare us, then
I will spare your daughter.

28:40.250 --> 28:41.580
Deal?

28:41.580 --> 28:44.080
♪♪

28:44.080 --> 28:46.500
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

28:46.500 --> 28:48.380
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

28:50.120 --> 28:52.670
Okay, everyone. Let's give
President Grant some privacy.

28:52.670 --> 28:54.080
Thank you all.

28:54.080 --> 28:56.210
My radiologist will be in
shortly to start your mammogram.

28:56.210 --> 28:58.170
Thank you,
Major General Owens.

28:58.170 --> 28:59.960
[ Clears throat ]

29:12.750 --> 29:14.170
Madam President.

29:14.170 --> 29:15.540
I'm sorry, Ms. Pope.
The president --

29:15.540 --> 29:16.580
It's okay, Chelsea.

29:24.120 --> 29:26.750
Have you made
your decision?

29:26.750 --> 29:28.000
I have.

29:32.460 --> 29:33.880
I won't be stepping down.

29:36.540 --> 29:38.920
[ Sighs ]

29:38.920 --> 29:40.670
I'm sorry to hear that.

29:40.670 --> 29:42.620
I'm sorry, too.

29:42.620 --> 29:44.670
I've scheduled a press
conference for tomorrow morning.

29:44.670 --> 29:46.210
Instead of announcing
my resignation,

29:46.210 --> 29:48.330
I'll be calling for yours.

29:48.330 --> 29:50.080
Is that so?

29:50.080 --> 29:54.420
♪♪

29:54.420 --> 29:56.620
[ Breathes deeply ]

29:56.620 --> 29:59.040
Mellie...

29:59.040 --> 30:01.000
I came here out of respect.

30:01.000 --> 30:04.290
To give you some advice
on the best way to resign.

30:04.290 --> 30:07.920
Be classy.
Show grace.

30:07.920 --> 30:11.460
And most importantly,

30:11.460 --> 30:14.670
take responsibility
for your actions.

30:14.670 --> 30:16.380
'Cause there are
women coming up the ranks,

30:16.380 --> 30:19.170
hoping for what
you have accomplished.

30:19.170 --> 30:21.580
And because
you were the first,

30:21.580 --> 30:25.210
any mistake you make
closes the door behind you.

30:25.210 --> 30:28.670
And I know how you would hate
for that to be your legacy.

30:28.670 --> 30:30.670
♪♪

30:30.670 --> 30:32.420
[ Sighs ]

30:32.420 --> 30:34.960
♪♪

30:34.960 --> 30:37.710
Good luck with your exam.

30:37.710 --> 30:41.120
Prevention
is the key to survival.

30:41.120 --> 30:47.120
♪♪

30:53.750 --> 30:55.580
Hey, where's Bobby Boy?
Uh, gone.

30:55.580 --> 30:57.790
He's rolling the dice
with the legal defense.

30:57.790 --> 30:59.290
Okay.
Well, what next?

30:59.290 --> 31:00.330
On to the next client?

31:00.330 --> 31:02.670
Should we start
placing ads or...

31:02.670 --> 31:03.670
What?

31:03.670 --> 31:05.250
Uh, maybe.

31:05.250 --> 31:07.120
Or...maybe we don't.

31:07.120 --> 31:09.580
What do you mean,
"maybe we don't"?

31:09.580 --> 31:11.120
You said the firm
was in danger of shutting down.

31:11.120 --> 31:13.500
I know. But maybe that's
the way it should be.

31:13.500 --> 31:14.830
Get out of town.
You're joking, right?

31:14.830 --> 31:16.290
I'm not.

31:16.290 --> 31:18.210
Working this case without Quinn?
I don't know.

31:18.210 --> 31:20.920
It --
It felt wrong.

31:20.920 --> 31:23.620
Without Quinn,
it -- it feels wrong.

31:23.620 --> 31:26.710
So maybe it's time to have
the harder conversation.

31:26.710 --> 31:28.040
What?! No!

31:28.040 --> 31:30.500
Not -- Look, I-I get it.
I do.

31:30.500 --> 31:32.000
I mean, maybe this was
just a bad client.

31:32.000 --> 31:33.670
Robert was a big zero.

31:33.670 --> 31:34.790
The next will be better.

31:34.790 --> 31:36.080
Or it'll be worse.

31:36.080 --> 31:37.710
Come on
with the attitude.

31:37.710 --> 31:39.000
It's not the same.

31:39.000 --> 31:41.330
It'll be the same.

31:41.330 --> 31:43.250
Eventually...

31:43.250 --> 31:44.830
it'll be
exactly the same.

31:44.830 --> 31:46.000
What are you talking about?

31:46.000 --> 31:49.790
♪♪

31:49.790 --> 31:52.710
[ Breathes deeply ]

31:52.710 --> 31:58.620
♪♪

31:58.620 --> 31:59.880
I'll be back.

31:59.880 --> 32:01.880
Just -- Just wait.

32:01.880 --> 32:07.000
♪♪

32:07.000 --> 32:09.790
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

32:09.790 --> 32:12.710
Charlie: Quinn!

32:12.710 --> 32:14.420
Quinn!

32:14.420 --> 32:16.330
[ Gun cocks ]

32:16.330 --> 32:17.750
What in God's name
are you doing?

32:17.750 --> 32:19.080
Looking for Quinn.

32:19.080 --> 32:20.960
What do you mean,
"looking for Quinn"?

32:20.960 --> 32:22.420
She left.

32:22.420 --> 32:23.920
An hour ago. With you.

32:23.920 --> 32:29.920
♪♪

32:30.170 --> 32:32.250
[ Sighs ]

32:32.250 --> 32:34.170
[ Robin coos ]

32:34.170 --> 32:40.170
♪♪

32:42.290 --> 32:48.290
♪♪

32:50.380 --> 32:56.380
♪♪

32:58.540 --> 33:04.580
♪♪

33:06.790 --> 33:09.710
Quinn: I know, I know.
She's the cutest.

33:09.710 --> 33:12.330
What? [ Gasps ]

33:12.330 --> 33:14.880
What is happening right now?
How are you here?

33:14.880 --> 33:17.040
I wanted you to see
your goddaughter.

33:17.040 --> 33:20.460
♪♪

33:20.460 --> 33:22.120
Once.

33:22.120 --> 33:25.290
♪♪

33:25.290 --> 33:27.920
Quinn. Please.

33:27.920 --> 33:29.750
Obviously there's a lot
I don't know.

33:29.750 --> 33:31.420
But there are things
you don't know, too.

33:31.420 --> 33:32.670
So, before --

33:32.670 --> 33:35.380
No talking this time.

33:35.380 --> 33:37.500
No pleading, no speeches.
No big, emotional appeals.

33:37.500 --> 33:39.040
You've already lost.
Quinn.

33:39.040 --> 33:41.500
Died and came back.
With a gun.

33:41.500 --> 33:42.790
You need to hear --

33:42.790 --> 33:44.670
Your confession.
I typed it all up for you.

33:44.670 --> 33:45.960
You're welcome.
Look it over.

33:45.960 --> 33:47.120
Everything's there.

33:47.120 --> 33:50.080
Rashad, Yasmeen,
conspiracy, murder, treason.

33:50.080 --> 33:51.420
You're going to sign that,

33:51.420 --> 33:52.620
turn it into David Rosen,
and then...

33:52.620 --> 33:53.670
Quinn, we can talk
all this out later,

33:53.670 --> 33:54.880
but right now
you're in danger.

33:54.880 --> 33:56.380
...you'll spend the rest
of your life in prison,

33:56.380 --> 33:59.420
where you'll be safe in case I
lose my admirable self-control.

33:59.420 --> 34:01.330
Since you died, you don't
think there were days

34:01.330 --> 34:02.710
that I wished I was dead, too?
No speeches.

34:02.710 --> 34:04.540
I deserved it.
I killed my best friend.

34:04.540 --> 34:06.250
No pleading!

34:06.250 --> 34:08.080
The thing is -- Even
if I wanted to die, I can't.

34:08.080 --> 34:09.420
I'm Command.
I'm too important.

34:09.420 --> 34:12.620
Right now, there are
B613-trained snipers

34:12.620 --> 34:13.710
across the street,

34:13.710 --> 34:15.250
and their scopes
are trained on you.

34:15.250 --> 34:17.380
You're bluffing.
Any second now,

34:17.380 --> 34:19.790
they're going to get tired
of you pointing that gun at me,

34:19.790 --> 34:21.830
and they're going to take
their shots at you.

34:21.830 --> 34:23.380
Rowan fell for your bluff.
I won't.
Unless you put that gun down.

34:23.380 --> 34:25.500
If you don't put the gun down,
you're going to die.

34:25.500 --> 34:27.830
This time for real, Quinn.
Would you shut up?!

34:27.830 --> 34:29.040
Shut up, or I --
Drop the gun!

34:29.040 --> 34:30.040
[ Gunshot, glass shatters ]

34:30.040 --> 34:32.790
[ Robin crying ]

34:32.790 --> 34:36.920
[ Groans, pants ]

34:36.920 --> 34:38.330
[ Groans ]

34:38.330 --> 34:39.960
[ Gasps ]

34:39.960 --> 34:41.500
Okay. Liv!

34:41.500 --> 34:47.500
♪♪

34:48.080 --> 34:51.040
Get out! Now!

34:51.040 --> 34:52.330
Go! Now!

34:52.330 --> 34:54.670
♪♪

35:01.790 --> 35:03.670
Madam President.
You wanted to see me.

35:03.670 --> 35:07.670
Olivia's arranged a press
conference for tomorrow morning.

35:07.670 --> 35:11.080
She knows.

35:11.080 --> 35:12.670
About Vanessa.
What we did.

35:12.670 --> 35:14.170
And she has evidence.

35:14.170 --> 35:15.830
A document, so...

35:18.580 --> 35:21.670
I'm going to admit to it.

35:21.670 --> 35:24.670
Take the fall
before things get any worse.

35:24.670 --> 35:27.080
I'm certain that whatever Olivia
has wouldn't hold up in court.

35:27.080 --> 35:28.580
We can still fight this.
No!

35:28.580 --> 35:30.710
It's over.

35:30.710 --> 35:32.500
[ Sighs ]

35:32.500 --> 35:34.460
I can leave your name out
of it, take this on myself.

35:34.460 --> 35:37.000
But once Cyrus is president?

35:37.000 --> 35:39.080
You're on your own.

35:39.080 --> 35:42.500
♪♪

35:42.500 --> 35:43.790
[ Sighs ]

35:43.790 --> 35:45.420
[ Doorbell rings ]

35:46.960 --> 35:48.670
Olivia.

35:48.670 --> 35:50.960
[ Gasps ]

35:55.960 --> 35:57.920
[ Gasps ]

35:57.920 --> 35:59.790
Rowan: Almost done.
Almost done.

36:02.670 --> 36:04.120
Almost done.

36:05.710 --> 36:07.290
You lied about Quinn.

36:07.290 --> 36:10.170
Ha! So did you.

36:10.170 --> 36:13.000
You claimed you didn't care
what happened to Quinn.

36:13.000 --> 36:14.710
That you weren't, uh...

36:14.710 --> 36:15.880
What was the phrase?

36:15.880 --> 36:17.790
"BFFs forever"?

36:17.790 --> 36:19.500
I was bluffing.
[ Laughs ]

36:19.500 --> 36:21.040
I know.

36:21.040 --> 36:23.920
Then why let me think
she was dead?

36:23.920 --> 36:25.250
[ Laughs ]

36:25.250 --> 36:26.830
Would you have
given me back my bones

36:26.830 --> 36:28.120
if you knew the truth?
No.

36:28.120 --> 36:29.170
Well, there's your answer.

36:31.250 --> 36:35.040
I just have to, uh,
bandage this up.

36:43.620 --> 36:45.790
She hates me, Dad.

36:45.790 --> 36:51.790
♪♪

36:52.830 --> 36:58.830
♪♪

36:59.830 --> 37:01.710
[ Chuckles ]

37:01.710 --> 37:07.710
♪♪

37:12.000 --> 37:15.880
There is a -- a debate
among paleontologists

37:15.880 --> 37:20.500
as to whether dinosaurs feel
love for their young or not.

37:20.500 --> 37:23.330
For many years, it seemed
that they -- they did not.

37:23.330 --> 37:26.670
Then one day,
a team in Montana

37:26.670 --> 37:29.380
discovered the remains
of the Maiasaura

37:29.380 --> 37:34.880
crouching over fossils
of three juveniles

37:34.880 --> 37:38.790
and 14 nests of eggs,

37:38.790 --> 37:40.540
protecting them.

37:40.540 --> 37:44.500
♪♪

37:44.500 --> 37:46.880
[ Chuckles ]

37:46.880 --> 37:48.670
It's something I've...

37:48.670 --> 37:52.170
been thinking about
a lot lately.

37:52.170 --> 37:55.380
[ Sobbing ]

37:55.380 --> 37:56.790
[ Sniffles ]

37:56.790 --> 38:01.580
♪♪

38:01.580 --> 38:03.120
[ Sniffles ]

38:03.120 --> 38:09.120
♪♪

38:11.500 --> 38:14.380
Be sure to clean it
twice a day.

38:14.380 --> 38:19.250
♪♪

38:19.250 --> 38:21.290
Try not to get it wet.

38:21.290 --> 38:27.290
♪♪

38:30.830 --> 38:32.250
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

38:32.250 --> 38:34.000
White House Chief of Staff
Olivia Pope

38:34.000 --> 38:36.540
will be issuing a public
statement this morning.

38:36.540 --> 38:38.420
There has been no word
as to what she might say,

38:38.420 --> 38:40.790
but insiders speculate
she will be announcing

38:40.790 --> 38:42.540
her rumored resignation.

38:57.170 --> 38:59.750
[ Indistinct conversations ]

38:59.750 --> 39:01.040
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

39:12.880 --> 39:15.670
When I was named
as Chief of Staff

39:15.670 --> 39:19.830
to the first female president
of the United States,

39:19.830 --> 39:23.710
I was filled with immense pride
and gratitude.

39:23.710 --> 39:25.330
Unfortunately...

39:42.460 --> 39:45.000
[ Ben E. King's "Stand by Me"
plays ]

39:45.000 --> 39:48.670
♪♪

39:48.670 --> 39:51.000
Unfortunately, my time
working for this administration

39:51.000 --> 39:52.750
has come to an end.

39:52.750 --> 39:57.920
Effective today, I am hereby
resigning as Chief of Staff

39:57.920 --> 39:59.880
to President Mellie Grant.

39:59.880 --> 40:04.710
This is not a decision
I came to lightly.

40:04.710 --> 40:06.580
Working in the White House

40:06.580 --> 40:09.670
came with its challenges,
certainly,

40:09.670 --> 40:14.330
but it also came
with extraordinary rewards.

40:14.330 --> 40:16.830
Reform
at the Justice Department.

40:16.830 --> 40:20.040
Free college. Nuclear
disarmament in the Middle East.

40:20.040 --> 40:23.120
These things
seemed like crazy dreams

40:23.120 --> 40:25.000
when the administration began,

40:25.000 --> 40:28.580
and today, they are realities.

40:28.580 --> 40:32.710
As proud as I am of
all we accomplished together,

40:32.710 --> 40:36.210
it's now time for me
to move on to other pursuits.

40:36.210 --> 40:38.420
To find some new crazy dreams.

40:38.420 --> 40:41.000
I guess we're not the only ones
who need new jobs.

40:41.000 --> 40:42.670
♪ Stand by me ♪

40:42.670 --> 40:44.670
♪ Stand by me ♪

40:44.670 --> 40:50.670
♪ If the sky that we look upon ♪

40:50.790 --> 40:52.000
♪ Should tumble and fall ♪

40:52.000 --> 40:53.380
Abby.

40:53.380 --> 40:55.250
What?

40:55.250 --> 40:57.880
♪ Should crumble to the sea ♪

40:57.880 --> 41:01.420
But I will always continue
to support President Grant

41:01.420 --> 41:03.250
in any capacity that I can.

41:03.250 --> 41:05.250
Because her dreams...

41:05.250 --> 41:07.500
♪ No, I won't ♪

41:07.500 --> 41:12.120
...her dreams
are bigger than all of us.

41:12.120 --> 41:15.670
They're the size of America.

41:15.670 --> 41:20.040
As diverse and vast
as this great nation.

41:20.040 --> 41:24.750
Her dreams take sacrifice...

41:24.750 --> 41:26.750
vision...

41:26.750 --> 41:30.460
courage.

41:30.460 --> 41:31.960
And fortunately
for the American people,

41:31.960 --> 41:33.620
she's not just a dreamer.

41:33.620 --> 41:35.120
She's a doer.

41:35.120 --> 41:37.620
A selfless public servant.

41:37.620 --> 41:41.040
An incomparable leader.

41:41.040 --> 41:43.960
She's the person
this country needs to unite us,

41:43.960 --> 41:47.960
to see us through
the tough times and the good.

41:47.960 --> 41:49.580
[ Robin crying ]

41:49.580 --> 41:53.540
♪♪

41:53.540 --> 41:55.250
On a personal note,

41:55.250 --> 41:59.000
I want to say thank you
to the president

41:59.000 --> 42:03.170
for the opportunity to serve,

42:03.170 --> 42:05.790
for her confidence in me,

42:05.790 --> 42:08.960
for her friendship.

42:08.960 --> 42:11.540
I hope I continue
to be worthy of it.

42:11.540 --> 42:13.040
Thank you.

42:13.040 --> 42:14.290
[ Indistinct shouting ]

42:14.290 --> 42:16.080
♪ Oh, stand ♪

42:16.080 --> 42:18.540
♪ Stand by me ♪

42:18.540 --> 42:20.580
♪ Whenever you're in trouble,
would you ♪

42:20.580 --> 42:23.120
♪ Stand by me? ♪

42:23.120 --> 42:25.250
♪ Oh, stand ♪

42:25.250 --> 42:26.080
♪ By me ♪

42:29.670 --> 42:35.670
♪♪

42:38.790 --> 42:44.790
♪♪

42:48.170 --> 42:54.170
♪♪
